                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-6">6. What are the prerequisites for the Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt course? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-6" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>There are no prerequisites for attending this Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt Certification course. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-1-7">7. What can I do after Six Sigma Yellow Belt? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-1-7" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-1">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The Six Sigma certifications are not one-size-fits-all certifications. After achieving the <b>Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt Training</b>, you can try for the Green Belt and Black Belt certifications. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cert-and-exam-section" id="lean-six-sigma-yellow-belt-certification-2">
                            <h3>Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt Certification</h3>
                            <div class="course-cert-faq-content accordion-cards custom-cards" id="faq-accordion-2">
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-1">1. What is Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-1" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belts are professionals who have been trained in the Six Sigma Yellow Belt training. They can understand and apply all the specifics of Six Sigma and can also work with and assist project teams.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-2">2. How Long Does It Take to Get a Six Sigma Yellow Belt?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-2" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>This varies from person to person. There is no fixed timeline for this certification. You need to learn the full curriculum <a href="#" target="_blank">under the course</a>, take the exam, and pass it. Only then will you be fully and properly certified.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-3">3. What is the difference between Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt and Six Sigma Yellow Belt?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-3" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The main difference between Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt and Six Sigma Yellow Belt is that Lean refers to reducing wastages in processes, while Six Sigma refers to reducing defects, improving quality, and processes.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-4">4. How will I get my Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt course completion certificate from KnowledgeHut?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-4" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You will receive your Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt course completion certificate in an e-mail from KnowledgeHut once you have successfully completed the course.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-5">5. Who provides the Yellow Belt certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-5" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Lean Six Sigma certifications are offered by the IASSC in partnership with PEOPLECERT. </p>
                                            <p>This is the first level of the Lean Six Sigma Certification scheme, and more advanced levels include the Lean Six Sigma Green Belt Certification, and the Lean Six Sigma Black Belt Certification.&nbsp;</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-6">6. Can I get Yellow Belt certified without taking the course?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-6" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Yes, you can get the Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt Certification without taking this course. The only requirement for certification is clearing the exam.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-7">7. How to get Six Sigma Yellow Belt certification? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-7" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>You can get the Six Sigma Yellow Belt Certification using the following steps: </p>
                                            <p><b>Step 1: Get Trained </b></p>
                                            <p>Enrol for an upcoming training program by KnowledgeHut an accredited training organization (ATO) with PeopleCert® and attend the 8-hour intensive training. </p>
                                            <p><b>Step 2: Take the IASSC Certified Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt Exam™ Exam </b></p>
                                            <p>Take the IASSC Certified Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt Exam™ exam and score a minimum of 70% in this 120-minute multiple choice exam. </p>
                                            <p><b>Step 3: Get Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt Certified &nbsp;</b></p>
                                            <p>Download the e-certificate. You are now a Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt certified professional. &nbsp;</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-8">8. Do you provide a course completion certificate?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-8" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Yes, you will receive a course completion certificate on successfully completing the Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt Certification course.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-9">9. How many times can I retake the exam?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-9" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>If you do not pass an IASSC Examination on your first try, you have to wait for at least two weeks after your first attempt to retake it. For a third attempt, there should be a gap of at least three months after the first. Any future exam attempts must take place at least three months after the most recent unsuccessful one.</p>
                                            <p>Each IASSC test ticket refers to just one exam attempt. If you don't pass, you must buy another exam voucher to want to take the exam again.</p>
                                            <p>Candidates for the ATA application only have one retake attempt. Candidates who failed both their first exam attempt and their retake can only reapply for accreditation six months after submitting their original application. </p>
                                            <p>For more details visit <a href="https://iassc.org/faqs/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">https://iassc.org/faqs/</a>.&nbsp;</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-10">10. Will my certificate say ‘Virtual’ if I take the certification online? </a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-10" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>No, your certificate will not mention the Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt Training was held online. It will look the same as the in-person certificates. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-11">11. Do I need to renew my Yellow Belt certification?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-11" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>No, the Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt certification is a lifetime certification and does not need to be renewed.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-12">12. Is the exam fee included in the Six Sigma Yellow Belt course fee?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-12" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>No, the exam fee is not included in the Six Sigma Yellow Belt Certification course fee. The price of the IASSC Certified Yellow Belt Exam is not included in the course fee. For more details visit <a href="https://iassc.org/faqs/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">https://iassc.org/faqs/</a>. </p>
                                            <p>If you still have any queries regarding the Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt Certification Cost, do reach out to us at support@knowledgehut.com and we will promptly address them. &nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-13">13. Is there an exam for Six Sigma Yellow Belt?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-13" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>Yes. To get the Six Sigma Yellow Belt, you need to pass a 2-hour exam containing 60 multiple-choice questions.&nbsp;<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="card">
                                    <div class="card-header"> <a class="card-link  collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq-heading-2-14">14. How hard is Six Sigma Yellow Belt exam?</a> </div>
                                    <div id="faq-heading-2-14" class="collapse " data-parent="#faq-accordion-2">
                                        <div class="card-body editor-content">
                                            <p>The Six Sigma Yellow Belt is a foundational certification. You will have to answer at least 70% of the 60 MCQs correctly in order to pass. So, it can be pretty hard depending on your preparation even though the Green Belt exam is tougher.<br></p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
