            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>This varies from person to person. There is no fixed timeline for this certification. You need to learn the full curriculum <a href=\"#\" target=\"_blank\">under the course</a>, take the exam, and pass it. Only then will you be fully and properly certified.&nbsp;<br></p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the difference between Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt and Six Sigma Yellow Belt?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The main difference between Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt and Six Sigma Yellow Belt is that Lean refers to reducing wastages in processes, while Six Sigma refers to reducing defects, improving quality, and processes.&nbsp;<br></p>"
            }
        }, {
