            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How many times can I retake the exam?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>If you do not pass an IASSC Examination on your first try, you have to wait for at least two weeks after your first attempt to retake it. For a third attempt, there should be a gap of at least three months after the first. Any future exam attempts must take place at least three months after the most recent unsuccessful one.</p><p>Each IASSC test ticket refers to just one exam attempt. If you don't pass, you must buy another exam voucher to want to take the exam again.</p><p>Candidates for the ATA application only have one retake attempt. Candidates who failed both their first exam attempt and their retake can only reapply for accreditation six months after submitting their original application. </p><p>For more details visit <a href=\"https://iassc.org/faqs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://iassc.org/faqs/</a>.&nbsp;</p>"
            }
